<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://score-theory.org/atlas#"
     xml:base="http://score-theory.org/atlas"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:core="http://score-theory.org/core#">

    <!-- ATLAS: multi-domain deterrence — the fourth SCORE implementation, the DOE prize
         (maximum domain contrast with POLARIS).
         A refinement P ⊆ S (see obsidian/SCORE/methodology/RefinementArchitecture.md).
         Q1–Q4 analysis: obsidian/SCORE/emergence/applications/ATLAS.md.
         Conformance: core ⊕ atlas must be consistent under HermiT (score_reason.py). -->
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas">
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core"/>
        <rdfs:comment>ATLAS implementation ontology — deterrence among state and corporate Sigma-actors across five domains (military, economic, information, energy, cultural). The maximum-domain-contrast peer: agreement with POLARIS in the SO/NS/closure intersection is the family's strongest universality test. SELECTs the core:SigmaInterventionClass taxonomy unchanged (its four NAryDeterrence pathways map onto the operators; the fourth, adjacent-possible constraint, maps onto core:AdjacentPossibleConstraint — the fifth SigmaInterventionClass operator, since promoted to core on the ATLAS n NEXUS intersection (NEXUS discharged this candidate)). Its HOA analog specializes core:HigherOrderAgent, not core:HumanCommunity — the first peer whose HOA-bearing collective is Sigma-actors rather than A-actors.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>Refinement conformance verified: core ⊕ atlas consistent, no unsatisfiable classes (HermiT via owlready2, 2026-06-04). Reproduce: scripts/score_reason.py.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>


    <!-- ── Fitness-criterion slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:FitnessCriterion) ──
         The THIRD filler of the slot ETHOS's Q3 promotion created — the slot is well past one-off. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#DeterrenceStability -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#DeterrenceStability">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#FitnessCriterion"/>
        <rdfs:label>Deterrence stability</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>ATLAS NS fitness criterion: neither escalation cascade nor capitulation. The deterrence basin is healthy when all actors' collective manifolds approximate the same B1 (the actual balance of capabilities and commitments) and the B3 signaling conventions are sufficient to prevent misinterpretation cascades across all active domains. Corporate actors integrated without accountability under the ontic trust are the primary contemporary instability source. Third filler of core:FitnessCriterion (after ethos:FloridiInformationHealth, agora:ManifoldCompatibility).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── Measurement-model slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:MeasurementModel) ── -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#BasinStabilityScore -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#BasinStabilityScore">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#MeasurementModel"/>
        <rdfs:label>Basin stability score</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>ATLAS attractor-health measurement model — the role-level SEWI analog (fills core:MeasurementModel; NOT a core:SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator — a structural composite, not a spectral trace processor). Composite of coupling density among actors in the stability basin, B3 signaling-convention coverage across domains (military high; economic/information/energy/cultural low to zero), misinterpretation-cascade risk (gap between signals sent and received across the reflexive chain), and corporate deterrence-relevant capability growth rate relative to governance-framework coverage. Domain-specific refinement; no BasinStabilityScore in core. A spectral EWS variant over the basin coupling-density trace is the named second-filler candidate for core:SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator (see SpectralEarlyWarningIndicator.md).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── HOA-analog slot filler (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:HigherOrderAgent) ──
         The first HOA analog that does NOT specialize core:HumanCommunity: ATLAS's HOA-bearing
         collective is a coupling structure among Sigma-actors, not a community of A-actors. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#DeterrenceBasin -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#DeterrenceBasin">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#HigherOrderAgent"/>
        <rdfs:label>Deterrence basin</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>ATLAS HOA analog: the multi-actor stability attractor in a strategic region or domain — a stable cycle in the coupledTo graph of major Sigma-actors whose persistence is determined by whether its sustaining constraints satisfy the Montevil-Mossio closure criterion. A HigherOrderAgent (has a HOA) whose constituents are Sigma-actors, not A-actors — the DOE-significant contrast with the HumanCommunity-based HOA analogs of POLARIS/ETHOS/AGORA. Crystallizes at the Erdos-Renyi coupledTo-density threshold (SigmaActorArchitecture S 2a).</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ── Sigma-actor specialization (Q2 SPECIALIZE of core:SigmaActor) ── -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#DeterrenceCoalition -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#DeterrenceCoalition">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#SigmaActor"/>
        <rdfs:label>Deterrence coalition</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>A crystallized alliance or coalition (NATO, BRICS, AUKUS) as a Sigma-actor whose constituents are themselves Sigma-actors — the entity a stable DeterrenceBasin sustains. Inherits the core Sigma-actor formation/maintenance axioms; its formal B3 commitment devices (mutual-defense clauses) are the coupledByTreaty layer made constitutive. Below the coherence threshold (coupledTo density too low for coordinated response) the coalition dissolves even though the treaty text persists.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>


    <!-- ════════════════ Phase C (2026-06-18): coverage-modulated signal reception ════════════════
         Reading (i), Q2 SPECIALIZE of the core:Incorporation morphism at the Sigma stratum (the
         Sigma-level dual of ethos:AmplificationFilteredIncorporation). ALSO ⊑ the promoted
         core:CollectiveManifoldUpdate — ATLAS is the second peer of the AGORA n ATLAS intersection
         (reception is AGORA's update operator under a coverage-distorted percept). The multiplicative
         fidelity decay sigma^k with reflexive depth is DL-inexpressible: Lean
         low_coverage_compounds_with_reflexive_depth (formal/Formal/Score/Atlas.lean See ATLAS-SignalingCascade.md. -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#receivedInDomain -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#receivedInDomain">
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#CoverageModulatedReception"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The domain a signal is received in; signaling-convention coverage sigma(d) varies sharply by domain (military high, others low), and reception distortion grows as coverage falls.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#CoverageModulatedReception -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#CoverageModulatedReception">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#Incorporation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#CollectiveManifoldUpdate"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#receivedInDomain"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>Coverage-modulated reception</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>ATLAS signal reception: a B3->collective-B2 incorporation modulated by signaling-convention coverage sigma(d). SPECIALIZEs core:Incorporation (reading (i), the Sigma-stratum incorporation-morphism contrast, DOEEvaluation gap #3) AND core:CollectiveManifoldUpdate (the second peer of the AGORA n ATLAS promotion — reception is AGORA's update operator under a coverage-distorted percept). The multiplicative fidelity decay sigma^k with reflexive depth is DL-inexpressible — Lean low_coverage_compounds_with_reflexive_depth (formal/Formal/Score/Atlas.lean See ATLAS-SignalingCascade.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain">
        <rdfs:comment>A domain across which Sigma-actors signal. The five domains below are pairwise disjoint; they differ in B3 signaling-convention coverage sigma (military high; economic / information / energy / cultural low to zero). Numeric sigma is Q4 BIND.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#MilitaryDomain -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#MilitaryDomain">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>High coverage: mature signaling conventions (hotlines, doctrine, treaty language) — signals received approximate signals sent.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#EconomicDomain -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#EconomicDomain">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Low coverage: sanctions and supply moves read ambiguously — no shared convention for intent.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#InformationDomain -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#InformationDomain">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Low to zero coverage: influence operations have no shared signaling convention — the most cascade-prone domain.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#EnergyDomain -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#EnergyDomain">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Low coverage: energy interdiction / supply signaling lacks conventionalized meaning.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#CulturalDomain -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#CulturalDomain">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/atlas#SignalingDomain"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Low to zero coverage: cultural / normative signaling has no shared convention across contrasting Sigma-actors.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

    <rdf:Description>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AllDisjointClasses"/>
        <owl:members rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#MilitaryDomain"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#EconomicDomain"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#InformationDomain"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#EnergyDomain"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#CulturalDomain"/>
        </owl:members>
    </rdf:Description>


    <!-- ── Doctrinal-region + composition fillers (Q2 SPECIALIZE of the promoted
         core:DoctrinalRegion / core:doctrinallyComposesFrom; eighth-promotion slot, 2026-06-21).
         DISTINCTIVE: the region-bearer is a Sigma-actor coalition (atlas:DeterrenceBasin ⊑
         core:HigherOrderAgent), NOT an A-actor HumanCommunity — so the region/fibration construct
         generalizes beyond A-actor communities. Lean formal/Formal/Score/Atlas.lean (atlasNetwork). -->

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#derivesFromDoctrine -->
    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#derivesFromDoctrine">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#doctrinallyComposesFrom"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Strategic-doctrine composition among B3 inscriptions: `y derivesFromDoctrine x` means grand strategy / doctrine y builds on substrate x (a strategic norm, a prior doctrine). The ATLAS instance of core:doctrinallyComposesFrom.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>

    <!-- http://score-theory.org/atlas#StrategicCorpus -->
    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://score-theory.org/atlas#StrategicCorpus">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://score-theory.org/core#DoctrinalRegion"/>
        <rdfs:label>Strategic corpus</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>The shared strategic doctrine a deterrence coalition (atlas:DeterrenceCoalition, in an atlas:DeterrenceBasin) holds: the graded down-set of the derivesFromDoctrine DAG. The ATLAS filler of core:DoctrinalRegion and the first region borne by a Sigma-actor collective rather than an A-actor community — evidence the construct is community-type-agnostic. Lean: formal/Formal/Score/Atlas.lean (atlasCorpus, atlasCorpus_isRegion). See ATLAS.md.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>

</rdf:RDF>
